fiscal  the rate of depreciation on laptop computers and cars increased from  and  to  and  respectively resulting in additional depreciation of rs million   c consequent to as  “accounting for taxes on income” issued by the institute of chartered accountants of india or icai becoming mandatory with effect from april   we have recorded the cumulative net deferred tax liability as at march   of rs million as a charge to the general reserve on april   and rs million against the accumulated profit and loss account   d in fiscal  we have with retrospective effect changed our method of accounting for finance leases in accordance with the as  “leases” issued by the icai consequent to the change the charge in fiscal  was lower by rs million including rs million in respect of previous fiscal years   e in view of the revised guidance note issued by the icai effective from the accounting period starting on or after april   which requires that provision should be made for excise duty liability in respect of bonded goods we have provided liability for excise duty and customs duty aggregating rs million payable on goods held in bond at the year end and therefore included the same in the valuation of inventories at the year end this had no effect on our profit for fiscal    f revenues in each of the years presented is net of excise duty collected from customers   g we have retroactively accounted for affiliates from april   for the purposes of this presentation  extraordinary exceptional items   a the extraordinary charge of rs million in fiscal  was comprised entirely of employee separation costs   b the extraordinary income of rs million in fiscal  represents writeback of provision for contingencies for a future trade investment made in fiscal     table of contents   c the extraordinary charge of rs million in fiscal  was comprised of provision for diminution in value of investments of rs million provision for contingencies of rs million and employee separation costs of rs million   d the extraordinary charge of rs million in fiscal  was comprised of employee separation costs of rs million and power costs relating to prior years of rs million  in fiscal  consequent to our shareholders’ approval and the order of the high court of judicature at mumbai dated may   tata motors ltd adjusted the debit balance of deferred revenue expenditure of rs million capital work in progress of rs million and diminution in the value of investment of rs million in its securities premium account the deferred tax liability of rs million created in respect thereof has been credited to its securities premium account   exchange rate information   for convenience some of the financial amounts presented in this registration statement have been translated from rupee amounts into dollar amounts at the rate of rs  us based on the noon buying rate for cable transfers as certified for customs purposes by the federal reserve bank of new york as of march   the date of our most recent balance sheet included in this registration statement however such translations do not imply that the rupee amounts have been could have been or could be converted into dollars at that or any other rate   the following table sets forth for the periods indicated information with respect to the exchange rate between the rupee and the dollar in rupees per dollar based on the average of the telegraphic transfer buying and selling rupeedollar exchange rates quoted by federal reserve bank of new york   period    periodend    periodaverage    high    low year ended march                   year ended march                   year ended march                   year ended march                   year ended march                   april                  may                  june                  july                  august  through august                   source federal reserve bank of new york   as of september   the rupeedollar noon buying rate quoted by federal reserve bank of new york was rs per us