ue to adverse change in the weighted average life in years or the discount rate   the above sensitivities are hypothetical and should be used with appropriate caution a  change in the assumptions may not result in lineally proportionate changes in the fair values of retained interests adverse changes assumed in the above analysis and resultant changes in the fair values of retained interests are calculated independently of each other in reality any change in one factor may cause changes in the other factors    inventories   inventories consist of the following        as of march                     in millions raw materials and manufacturing supplies    rs      rs      us   work in progress                   finished products                              total    rs      rs      us                f table of contents  prepaid expenses and other current assets   prepaid expenses and other current assets consist of the following        as of march                     in millions advances to suppliers contractors and others    rs      rs      us  deposits with government and public bodies                   prepaid expenses                   advance taxes net                   other current assets                              total    rs     rs     us                 investments   investments consist of the following        as of march                     in millions investments available for sale at market    rs     rs     us   investments held to maturity at amortized cost                   investments at cost net                              total    rs      rs      us               information on unrealized gains and losses for investments available for sale is as follows   available for sale securities    amortizedcost    grossunrealizedgains    grossunrealizedlosses    fair value      in millions as of march                               equity shares    rs     rs      rs      rs                    retained interests in securitized transactions                     